---
import CaseStudyLayout from '../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro';

const nav = [
  { label: 'Overview', href: '#overview' },
  { label: 'Branding', href: '#branding' },
  { label: 'Template', href: '#template' },
  { label: 'Website', href: '#website' },
  { label: 'Reflection', href: '#reflection' },
];
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  title="GWSK"
  heading="Building an Enduring Identity for GWSK"
  role="Design Intern"
  team="Design Intern, Stakeholder/PM"
  timeline="3.5 weeks"
  projectType="Brand Design, Web Design"
  nav={nav}
>
  <section id="overview">
    <h3>context</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      I collaborated with another intern to reimagine the studio's brand identity and website. We
      built a cohesive, transit-inspired system that brought personality and consistency to the
      brand.
    </p>
    <h3>final result</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      Built a full brand system with reusable templates and redesigned the website, achieving an
      83.3% scroll depth on mobile.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://gwsk.studio/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="font-medium underline decoration-ink/30 underline-offset-4"
      >
        GWSK Website
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="branding">
    <h3>brand tone</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      Brutalist, smart, minimal, confident, Bauhaus-inspired, and accessible. Refined but human,
      modular but not robotic.
    </p>
    <h3>Research</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      We were suggested to reference Landon Nordeman, Zaha Hadid, Pentagram, Teenage Engineering,
      and the Bauhaus and Brutalist movement when ideating.
    </p>
    <h3>final concept</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      Modular, TTC transit system inspired visual language to communicate the systematic and
      accessible approach GWSK brings to product design. Each accent colour represents a stage of the
      Double Diamond Process.
    </p>
    <p>
      We created type styles, colour variables, effect styles, layout grid styles, as well as
      components for visual assets and plugin use cases.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="template">
    <h3>Presentation Deck</h3>
    <p>
      Slide decks are colour coded based on the step of the design process the deck has content
      correlates to. Plugins were linked for data visualization slides for easy data entry. Animated
      key interactions in slide deck.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="website">
    <h3>website review</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      The existing website is responsive, with good visual hierarchy and colour accessibility, but
      lacks personality and could have a more emphasized CTA to book a meeting.
    </p>
    <h3>redesign objective</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <h2>Represent GWSK's style and design philosophy</h2>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Show GWSK's design process and services</h2>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Encourage potential clients to book a meeting</h2>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <h3>process</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      Due to the tight time constraint, the other intern and I rapidly iterated between design and
      implementation to see what is feasible and what isn't.
    </p>
    <h3>Responsiveness</h3>
    <p class="lead">
      I had to wear both design and dev hats through the process. Here's an example of the
      responsiveness issues we faced along the way.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="reflection">
    <h3>Reflections</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <h2>Design process is not linear!</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          The process is highly iterative and doesn't always follow a clear linear trajectory.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Work under a time crunch</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Prioritize key deliverables and communicate frequently to make necessary pivots.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Wear multiple hats</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Think about technical constraints and think of backup plans when implementing.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
    <h3 class="!mt-12">next steps</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <h2>Pre-launch usability testing</h2>
        <p class="lead">Identify any changes needed to make the design more intuitive.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Quantify outcomes</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Compare the conversion rate of users (How many clicked book a meeting)
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <h2>Evaluate visual communication</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Interview users about their experience and impression of GWSK to see if the brand vision
          is communicated.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>
</CaseStudyLayout>
